.SS Known issues
.sp
Even though possible by using multiple sessions, the library is not suitable to connect to a large number of IRC servers simultaneously. If you still want to use it, you\(aqd have to overcome the following:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
You cannot use the main loop in \fBirc_run()\fP because it only supports one session. You would have to use \fBirc_add_select_descriptors()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
You\(aqd have to handle reconnections separately by processing the relevant \fBirc_process_select_descriptors()\fP return values
.IP \(bu 2
If you wish to use poll/epoll() instead of select() you\(aqd have to write more logic as it is not directly supported. See the \fIFAQ\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
The library is not optimized to have a low per\-connection memory footprint, each non\-SSL connection uses at least 4K, with around 32K per connection for SSL.
